	The first edition of CG Magazine's new digital only issue.

	In this issue we take a look at how gamers and comic book fans are interacting 
	with one another, and the digital generation is changing.

	We take a look at comic book creators working thousands of kilometers from 
	one another, why no one is talking on voice chat anymore, and how games like Rust are 
	changing how we play multiplayer.

	We also have the usual reviews and editorial commentary on the videogame and comic 
	communities, so check it all out in the March 2014 issue of CG Magazine.
